casebody.data:
UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Miguel Angel RUIZ-CABANILLAS, also known as Ricardo, Defendant-Appellant No. 15-10294

Conference Calendar

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Date Filed: 06/21/2016 James Wesley Hendrix, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Northern District of Texas, Dallas, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Miguel Angel Ruiz-Cabanillas, Adelanto, CA, Pro Se. Before JONES, CLEMENT, and OWEN, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Miguel Angel Ruiz-Cabanillas has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed briefs in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967), and United States v. Flores, 632 F.3d 229 (5th Cir. 2011). Ruiz-Cabanillas has not filed a response. We have reviewed counsel’s briefs and the relevant portions of the record reflected therein. We concur with counsel’s assessment that the appeal presents no nonfrivolous issue for appellate review. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.21

Pursuant to 5th Cm. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
